    &gt;     &gt; 
    &gt;     &gt; Which JDK are you using?  You could also use the 
    &gt;     &gt; -Xrunhprof option (I think
    &gt;     &gt; it is only available 1.2.x +).  Use the attached tail.exe 
    &gt;     &gt; to tail the file.
    &gt;     &gt; See 
    &gt;     &gt; &lt;http://java.sun.com/products/jdk/1.2/docs/guide/jvmpi/jvm
    &gt;     &gt; pi.html#hprof&gt;
    &gt;     &gt; for how to interpret -Xrunhprof, but basically you 
    &gt; are looking for
    &gt;     &gt; ThreadStarts that don&#39;t have an associated ThreadEnd.  
    &gt;     &gt; This will tell you
    &gt;     &gt; where possible hangs are happening.
    &gt;     &gt; 
    &gt;     &gt; -Jason
