    &gt;     &gt;     &gt; 
    &gt;     &gt;     &gt; 
    &gt;     &gt;     &gt; Run your tests with the text test runner.  When 
    &gt;     &gt; it&#39;s hung do a
    &gt;     &gt;     &gt; Ctrl-Break (on unix you have to send a 
    &gt; signal, not sure 
    &gt;     &gt;     &gt; which one).
    &gt;     &gt;     &gt; This causes the JVM to do a thread dump.  You 
    &gt; can see a 
    &gt;     &gt;     &gt; stack trace of
    &gt;     &gt;     &gt; each thread and hopefully find your deadlock.
